---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import { Code } from "astro:components";
import { withBase } from "../../utils/url";

const toc = [
  { id: "not-found", title: "Adapter not found", level: 2 as const },
  { id: "indentation", title: "IndentationError", level: 2 as const },
  { id: "no-burla", title: "burla client not installed", level: 2 as const },
  { id: "unreachable", title: "Cluster unreachable", level: 2 as const },
  { id: "not-df", title: "Must return DataFrame", level: 2 as const },
  { id: "not-preloaded", title: "Upstream not pre-loaded", level: 2 as const },
  { id: "dbt-tmp", title: "Table __dbt_tmp missing", level: 2 as const },
  { id: "hangs", title: "Model hangs", level: 2 as const },
  { id: "resource-warn", title: "pytest ResourceWarning", level: 2 as const },
  { id: "sf-binding", title: "Snowflake binding error", level: 2 as const },
  { id: "bq-access", title: "BigQuery access denied", level: 2 as const },
];
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Troubleshooting"
  description="Common dbt-burla issues and fixes."
  lede="Something broke. Start here before opening an issue — most problems are one of the patterns below."
  crumbs={[{ title: "Docs", href: withBase("/docs/") }]}
  toc={toc}
  prev={{ title: "Configuration reference", href: withBase("/docs/configuration/") }}
>
  <h2 id="not-found">"Could not find adapter type burla_*"</h2>
  <p>
    <code>pip install "dbt-burla[&lt;warehouse&gt;]"</code> didn't complete, or you're in a
    different virtualenv than dbt itself. Verify:
  </p>
  <Code code={`python -c "from dbt.adapters.burla_duckdb import Plugin; print(Plugin)"`} lang="bash" theme="github-dark-dimmed" />

  <h2 id="indentation">"IndentationError: unexpected indent" during a Python model</h2>
  <p>dbt emits compiled code with leading whitespace; dbt-burla strips this automatically. If you're seeing this, you're on a very old version — upgrade.</p>

  <h2 id="no-burla">"The `burla` client isn't installed"</h2>
  <p><code>pip install burla</code> (should be pulled in automatically). Or set <code>burla_fake: true</code> in your profile to run in-process.</p>

  <h2 id="unreachable">"Burla cluster unreachable at ..."</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><code>burla login</code> was run and credentials are in <code>~/.config/burla/</code>.</li>
    <li><code>burla_cluster_url</code> in your profile matches your cluster.</li>
    <li><code>BURLA_CLUSTER_DASHBOARD_URL</code> env var isn't set to something stale.</li>
  </ol>
  <Code code={`python -c "from burla import get_cluster_dashboard_url; print(get_cluster_dashboard_url())"`} lang="bash" theme="github-dark-dimmed" />

  <h2 id="not-df">"Python model must return a pandas DataFrame"</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Returning a <code>list</code> or <code>dict</code> — wrap with <code>pd.DataFrame(...)</code>.</li>
    <li>Returning a Polars / pyarrow object — convert first: <code>df.to_pandas()</code>.</li>
    <li>Forgetting the <code>return</code> statement.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="not-preloaded">"Upstream relation was not pre-loaded"</h2>
  <p>dbt didn't include the relation in the compiled refs/sources dict. Usually:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>You're constructing the <code>dbt.ref()</code> name dynamically. Use static strings.</li>
    <li>A ref exists in dbt's DAG but isn't in your model's <code>depends_on</code>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="dbt-tmp">"Catalog Error: Table with name X__dbt_tmp does not exist"</h2>
  <p>Old version before the custom DuckDB materialization. Upgrade to <code>&gt;=0.1.0</code>.</p>

  <h2 id="hangs">Python model runs forever / hangs on Burla</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>The Burla cluster is cold-starting workers (first run takes longer).</li>
    <li>Your <code>burla_image</code> is large and being pulled.</li>
    <li>Your <code>model()</code> has a synchronous network call without a timeout.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Set <code>burla_timeout_s</code> on the model to fail fast.</p>

  <h2 id="resource-warn">CI pytest fails with "ResourceWarning: unclosed file"</h2>
  <Code code={`[tool.pytest.ini_options]
filterwarnings = [
    "ignore::ResourceWarning",
    "ignore::pytest.PytestUnraisableExceptionWarning",
]`} lang="toml" theme="github-dark-dimmed" />

  <h2 id="sf-binding">Snowflake: "Binding data in type is not supported"</h2>
  <p><code>write_pandas</code> can't handle every pandas dtype. Convert before returning:</p>
  <Code code={`df["my_col"] = df["my_col"].astype(str)
return df`} lang="python" theme="github-dark-dimmed" />

  <h2 id="bq-access">BigQuery: "Access Denied" during load_table_from_dataframe</h2>
  <p>Service account needs both <code>bigquery.dataEditor</code> and <code>bigquery.jobUser</code>. <code>dbt debug</code> only tests SELECT.</p>

  <h2>Still stuck?</h2>
  <p>
    Open an issue at <a href="https://github.com/Burla-Cloud/dbt-burla/issues">github.com/Burla-Cloud/dbt-burla/issues</a> with:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>dbt --version</code></li>
    <li>Full <code>dbt run --debug</code> output</li>
    <li>Your Python model (redacted)</li>
    <li>Warehouse variant</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
